resource.name: LDAP Server (OpenLDAP) over new LDAPConn.
resource.description: LDAP resource using new LDAP Connector based on Apache Directory API. It contains configuration for connecting to an OpenLDAP instance running on the localhost.

script.code:
import javax.naming.ldap.Rdn import javax.naming.ldap.LdapName
dn = new LdapName('ou=Projects,dc=example,dc=com') dn.add(new Rdn('cn', name.toString())) return dn.toString()

expression.description: Expression that assigns a fixed description value if there is no other description present.

correlation.q:description: Correlation expression is a search query. Following search queury will look for users that have "name" equal to the "uid" attribute of the account. Simply speaking, it will look for match in usernames in the IDM and the resource. The correlation rule always looks for users, so it will not match any other object type.
